ision in the context of theories of aesthetic experience and identifies a semantics of seeing. It analyses functions of symbolic materiality in the presentation of boundaries of perception, modes of temporality and poetic potentialities. In exploring the connections between vision and language, it seeks to provide new perspectives for a reassessment of what occurs in Modernism's relation to vision.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aaesthetics, visualization, modernity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Literary and Cultural Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023846408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103935140 cprintz978311034022840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034023540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110340235423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110340235/original  a978-3-11-023846-4  DGBA Backlist Literary and Cultural Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-074296-1  De Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aE